eNCA contributor Mpho Lakaje has this special Freedom Day report. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - 28-years ago, millions of South Africans woke up bright and early to join long queues across the nation. 27 April 1994, was a special day for the majority of South Africans who voted in democratic elections, for the very first time but then, if your loved one, who contributed to the fight against apartheid, remains missing to this day, what’s there to celebrate? How do you even find closure and move on, when no one is prepared to come forward with the truth? READ: Freedom Day | Fast facts about Election Day in 1994 This is the pain Johannesburg resident Bafana Nkuta and hundreds of others, live with. eNCA contributor Mpho Lakaje has this special Freedom Day report in the video above. 